{
    "language": "en",
    "text": [
        {
            "text": "What is so special about the human brain?",
            "start": 12.946,
            "duration": 2.394
        },
        {
            "text": "Why is it that we study other animals",
            "start": 15.34,
            "duration": 2.212
        },
        {
            "text": "instead of them studying us?",
            "start": 17.552,
            "duration": 2.121
        },
        {
            "text": "What does a human brain have or do",
            "start": 19.673,
            "duration": 1.798
        },
        {
            "text": "that no other brain does?",
            "start": 21.471,
            "duration": 1.733
        },
        {
            "text": "When I became interested\nin these questions about 10 years ago,",
            "start": 23.204,
            "duration": 2.848
        },
        {
            "text": "scientists thought they knew\nwhat different brains were made of.",
            "start": 26.052,
            "duration": 2.942
        },
        {
            "text": "Though it was based on very little evidence,",
            "start": 28.994,
            "duration": 1.729
        },
        {
            "text": "many scientists thought that all mammalian brains,",
            "start": 30.723,
            "duration": 2.187
        },
        {
            "text": "including the human brain,",
            "start": 32.91,
            "duration": 1.725
        },
        {
            "text": "were made in the same way,",
            "start": 34.635,
            "duration": 1.3
        },
        {
            "text": "with a number of neurons that was always",
            "start": 35.935,
            "duration": 1.502
        },
        {
            "text": "proportional to the size of the brain.",
            "start": 37.437,
            "duration": 2.231
        },
        {
            "text": "This means that two brains of the same size,",
            "start": 39.668,
            "duration": 2.076
        },
        {
            "text": "like these two, with a respectable 400 grams,",
            "start": 41.744,
            "duration": 3.548
        },
        {
            "text": "should have similar numbers of neurons.",
            "start": 45.292,
            "duration": 2.552
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, if neurons are the functional",
            "start": 47.844,
            "duration": 1.796
        },
        {
            "text": "information processing units of the brain,",
            "start": 49.64,
            "duration": 2.903
        },
        {
            "text": "then the owners of these two brains",
            "start": 52.543,
            "duration": 1.592
        },
        {
            "text": "should have similar cognitive abilities.",
            "start": 54.135,
            "duration": 2.729
        },
        {
            "text": "And yet, one is a chimp,",
            "start": 56.864,
            "duration": 2.349
        },
        {
            "text": "and the other is a cow.",
            "start": 59.213,
            "duration": 2.637
        },
        {
            "text": "Now maybe cows have a really rich",
            "start": 61.85,
            "duration": 2.362
        },
        {
            "text": "internal mental life and are so smart",
            "start": 64.212,
            "duration": 2.253
        },
        {
            "text": "that they choose not to let us realize it,",
            "start": 66.465,
            "duration": 3.803
        },
        {
            "text": "but we eat them.",
            "start": 70.268,
            "duration": 1.445
        },
        {
            "text": "I think most people will agree",
            "start": 71.713,
            "duration": 1.699
        },
        {
            "text": "that chimps are capable of much more complex,",
            "start": 73.412,
            "duration": 2.001
        },
        {
            "text": "elaborate and flexible behaviors than cows are.",
            "start": 75.413,
            "duration": 3.056
        },
        {
            "text": "So this is a first indication that the",
            "start": 78.469,
            "duration": 1.932
        },
        {
            "text": "\"all brains are made the same way\" scenario",
            "start": 80.401,
            "duration": 2.033
        },
        {
            "text": "is not quite right.",
            "start": 82.434,
            "duration": 1.671
        },
        {
            "text": "But let's play along.",
            "start": 84.105,
            "duration": 1.346
        },
        {
            "text": "If all brains were made the same way",
            "start": 85.451,
            "duration": 1.778
        },
        {
            "text": "and you were to compare animals\nwith brains of different sizes,",
            "start": 87.229,
            "duration": 2.912
        },
        {
            "text": "larger brains should always have more neurons",
            "start": 90.141,
            "duration": 2.182
        },
        {
            "text": "than smaller brains,\nand the larger the brain,",
            "start": 92.323,
            "duration": 2.323
        },
        {
            "text": "the more cognitively able its owner should be.",
            "start": 94.646,
            "duration": 3.022
        },
        {
            "text": "So the largest brain around should also be",
            "start": 97.668,
            "duration": 2.136
        },
        {
            "text": "the most cognitively able.",
            "start": 99.804,
            "duration": 2.289
        },
        {
            "text": "And here comes the bad news:",
            "start": 102.093,
            "duration": 1.581
        },
        {
            "text": "Our brain, not the largest one around.",
            "start": 103.674,
            "duration": 2.757
        },
        {
            "text": "It seems quite vexing.",
            "start": 106.431,
            "duration": 1.555
        },
        {
            "text": "Our brain weighs between 1.2 and 1.5 kilos,",
            "start": 107.986,
            "duration": 2.735
        },
        {
            "text": "but elephant brains weigh between four and five kilos,",
            "start": 110.721,
            "duration": 3.317
        },
        {
            "text": "and whale brains can weigh up to nine kilos,",
            "start": 114.038,
            "duration": 2.585
        },
        {
            "text": "which is why scientists used to resort to saying",
            "start": 116.623,
            "duration": 4.738
        },
        {
            "text": "that our brain must be special",
            "start": 121.361,
            "duration": 2.157
        },
        {
            "text": "to explain our cognitive abilities.",
            "start": 123.518,
            "duration": 2.862
        },
        {
            "text": "It must be really extraordinary,",
            "start": 126.38,
            "duration": 2.946
        },
        {
            "text": "an exception to the rule.",
            "start": 129.326,
            "duration": 1.977
        },
        {
            "text": "Theirs may be bigger, but ours is better,",
            "start": 131.303,
            "duration": 3.226
        },
        {
            "text": "and it could be better, for example,",
            "start": 134.529,
            "duration": 1.875
        },
        {
            "text": "in that it seems larger than it should be,",
            "start": 136.404,
            "duration": 2.111
        },
        {
            "text": "with a much larger cerebral cortex\nthan we should have",
            "start": 138.515,
            "duration": 2.698
        },
        {
            "text": "for the size of our bodies.",
            "start": 141.213,
            "duration": 1.539
        },
        {
            "text": "So that would give us extra cortex",
            "start": 142.752,
            "duration": 1.652
        },
        {
            "text": "to do more interesting things\nthan just operating the body.",
            "start": 144.404,
            "duration": 2.96
        },
        {
            "text": "That's because the size of the brain",
            "start": 147.364,
            "duration": 1.679
        },
        {
            "text": "usually follows the size of the body.",
            "start": 149.043,
            "duration": 2.333
        },
        {
            "text": "So the main reason for saying that",
            "start": 151.376,
            "duration": 2.317
        },
        {
            "text": "our brain is larger than it should be",
            "start": 153.693,
            "duration": 2.087
        },
        {
            "text": "actually comes from comparing ourselves",
            "start": 155.78,
            "duration": 1.772
        },
        {
            "text": "to great apes.",
            "start": 157.552,
            "duration": 1.686
        },
        {
            "text": "Gorillas can be two to three times larger than we are,",
            "start": 159.238,
            "duration": 2.594
        },
        {
            "text": "so their brains should also be larger than ours,",
            "start": 161.832,
            "duration": 2.421
        },
        {
            "text": "but instead it's the other way around.",
            "start": 164.253,
            "duration": 1.945
        },
        {
            "text": "Our brain is three times larger than a gorilla brain.",
            "start": 166.198,
            "duration": 2.935
        },
        {
            "text": "The human brain also seems special",
            "start": 169.133,
            "duration": 2.12
        },
        {
            "text": "in the amount of energy that it uses.",
            "start": 171.253,
            "duration": 2.247
        },
        {
            "text": "Although it weighs only two percent of the body,",
            "start": 173.5,
            "duration": 2.749
        },
        {
            "text": "it alone uses 25 percent of all the energy",
            "start": 176.249,
            "duration": 3.443
        },
        {
            "text": "that your body requires to run per day.",
            "start": 179.692,
            "duration": 2.463
        },
        {
            "text": "That's 500 calories out of a total of 2,000 calories,",
            "start": 182.155,
            "duration": 3.353
        },
        {
            "text": "just to keep your brain working.",
            "start": 185.508,
            "duration": 2.405
        },
        {
            "text": "So the human brain is larger than it should be,",
            "start": 187.913,
            "duration": 2.928
        },
        {
            "text": "it uses much more energy than it should,",
            "start": 190.841,
            "duration": 2.026
        },
        {
            "text": "so it's special.",
            "start": 192.867,
            "duration": 1.458
        },
        {
            "text": "And this is where the story started to bother me.",
            "start": 194.325,
            "duration": 2.571
        },
        {
            "text": "In biology, we look for rules",
            "start": 196.896,
            "duration": 1.671
        },
        {
            "text": "that apply to all animals and to life in general,",
            "start": 198.567,
            "duration": 2.846
        },
        {
            "text": "so why should the rules of evolution",
            "start": 201.413,
            "duration": 1.85
        },
        {
            "text": "apply to everybody else but not to us?",
            "start": 203.263,
            "duration": 3.642
        },
        {
            "text": "Maybe the problem was with the basic assumption",
            "start": 206.905,
            "duration": 2.197
        },
        {
            "text": "that all brains are made in the same way.",
            "start": 209.102,
            "duration": 1.871
        },
        {
            "text": "Maybe two brains of a similar size",
            "start": 210.973,
            "duration": 1.599
        },
        {
            "text": "can actually be made of\nvery different numbers of neurons.",
            "start": 212.572,
            "duration": 2.591
        },
        {
            "text": "Maybe a very large brain",
            "start": 215.163,
            "duration": 1.607
        },
        {
            "text": "does not necessarily have more neurons",
            "start": 216.77,
            "duration": 1.84
        },
        {
            "text": "than a more modest-sized brain.",
            "start": 218.61,
            "duration": 2.221
        },
        {
            "text": "Maybe the human brain \nactually has the most neurons",
            "start": 220.831,
            "duration": 3.009
        },
        {
            "text": "of any brain, regardless of its size,",
            "start": 223.84,
            "duration": 2.573
        },
        {
            "text": "especially in the cerebral cortex.",
            "start": 226.413,
            "duration": 2.094
        },
        {
            "text": "So this to me became",
            "start": 228.507,
            "duration": 1.552
        },
        {
            "text": "the important question to answer:",
            "start": 230.059,
            "duration": 1.729
        },
        {
            "text": "how many neurons does the human brain have,",
            "start": 231.788,
            "duration": 2.4
        },
        {
            "text": "and how does that compare to other animals?",
            "start": 234.188,
            "duration": 2.522
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, you may have heard or read somewhere",
            "start": 236.71,
            "duration": 2.423
        },
        {
            "text": "that we have 100 billion neurons,",
            "start": 239.133,
            "duration": 2.111
        },
        {
            "text": "so 10 years ago, I asked my colleagues",
            "start": 241.244,
            "duration": 2.086
        },
        {
            "text": "if they knew where this number came from.",
            "start": 243.33,
            "duration": 1.839
        },
        {
            "text": "But nobody did.",
            "start": 245.169,
            "duration": 1.458
        },
        {
            "text": "I've been digging through the literature",
            "start": 246.627,
            "duration": 1.453
        },
        {
            "text": "for the original reference for that number,",
            "start": 248.08,
            "duration": 2.058
        },
        {
            "text": "and I could never find it.",
            "start": 250.138,
            "duration": 1.783
        },
        {
            "text": "It seems that nobody had actually ever counted",
            "start": 251.921,
            "duration": 2.739
        },
        {
            "text": "the number of neurons in the human brain,",
            "start": 254.66,
            "duration": 1.534
        },
        {
            "text": "or in any other brain for that matter.",
            "start": 256.194,
            "duration": 2.499
        },
        {
            "text": "So I came up with my own way\nto count cells in the brain,",
            "start": 258.693,
            "duration": 3.535
        },
        {
            "text": "and it essentially consists of",
            "start": 262.228,
            "duration": 2.108
        },
        {
            "text": "dissolving that brain into soup.",
            "start": 264.336,
            "duration": 3.245
        },
        {
            "text": "It works like this:",
            "start": 267.581,
            "duration": 2.037
        },
        {
            "text": "You take a brain, or parts of that brain,",
            "start": 269.618,
            "duration": 3.127
        },
        {
            "text": "and you dissolve it in detergent,",
            "start": 272.745,
            "duration": 1.744
        },
        {
            "text": "which destroys the cell membranes",
            "start": 274.489,
            "duration": 1.509
        },
        {
            "text": "but keeps the cell nuclei intact,",
            "start": 275.998,
            "duration": 2.436
        },
        {
            "text": "so you end up with a suspension of free nuclei",
            "start": 278.434,
            "duration": 3.14
        },
        {
            "text": "that looks like this,",
            "start": 281.574,
            "duration": 1.781
        },
        {
            "text": "like a clear soup.",
            "start": 283.355,
            "duration": 1.273
        },
        {
            "text": "This soup contains all the nuclei",
            "start": 284.628,
            "duration": 1.891
        },
        {
            "text": "that once were a mouse brain.",
            "start": 286.519,
            "duration": 2.054
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, the beauty of a soup is that because it is soup,",
            "start": 288.573,
            "duration": 3.03
        },
        {
            "text": "you can agitate it and make those nuclei",
            "start": 291.603,
            "duration": 2.898
        },
        {
            "text": "be distributed homogeneously in the liquid,",
            "start": 294.501,
            "duration": 1.971
        },
        {
            "text": "so that now by looking under the microscope",
            "start": 296.472,
            "duration": 1.981
        },
        {
            "text": "at just four or five samples\nof this homogeneous solution,",
            "start": 298.453,
            "duration": 4.083
        },
        {
            "text": "you can count nuclei, and therefore tell",
            "start": 302.536,
            "duration": 2.536
        },
        {
            "text": "how many cells that brain had.",
            "start": 305.072,
            "duration": 1.679
        },
        {
            "text": "It's simple, it's straightforward,",
            "start": 306.751,
            "duration": 1.625
        },
        {
            "text": "and it's really fast.",
            "start": 308.376,
            "duration": 1.434
        },
        {
            "text": "So we've used that method to count neurons",
            "start": 309.81,
            "duration": 1.997
        },
        {
            "text": "in dozens of different species so far,",
            "start": 311.807,
            "duration": 2.311
        },
        {
            "text": "and it turns out that all brains",
            "start": 314.118,
            "duration": 1.689
        },
        {
            "text": "are not made the same way.",
            "start": 315.807,
            "duration": 2.582
        },
        {
            "text": "Take rodents and primates, for instance:",
            "start": 318.389,
            "duration": 2.187
        },
        {
            "text": "In larger rodent brains, the average size",
            "start": 320.576,
            "duration": 2.284
        },
        {
            "text": "of the neuron increases,",
            "start": 322.86,
            "duration": 1.686
        },
        {
            "text": "so the brain inflates very rapidly",
            "start": 324.546,
            "duration": 2.599
        },
        {
            "text": "and gains size much faster than it gains neurons.",
            "start": 327.145,
            "duration": 3.165
        },
        {
            "text": "But primate brains gain neurons",
            "start": 330.31,
            "duration": 1.703
        },
        {
            "text": "without the average neuron becoming any larger,",
            "start": 332.013,
            "duration": 2.459
        },
        {
            "text": "which is a very economical way",
            "start": 334.472,
            "duration": 1.525
        },
        {
            "text": "to add neurons to your brain.",
            "start": 335.997,
            "duration": 1.653
        },
        {
            "text": "The result is that a primate brain",
            "start": 337.65,
            "duration": 1.764
        },
        {
            "text": "will always have more neurons than\na rodent brain of the same size,",
            "start": 339.414,
            "duration": 3.167
        },
        {
            "text": "and the larger the brain,",
            "start": 342.581,
            "duration": 1.483
        },
        {
            "text": "the larger this difference will be.",
            "start": 344.064,
            "duration": 2.214
        },
        {
            "text": "Well, what about our brain then?",
            "start": 346.278,
            "duration": 2.103
        },
        {
            "text": "We found that we have, on average,",
            "start": 348.381,
            "duration": 1.684
        },
        {
            "text": "86 billion neurons,",
            "start": 350.065,
            "duration": 1.785
        },
        {
            "text": "16 billion of which are in the cerebral cortex,",
            "start": 351.85,
            "duration": 2.999
        },
        {
            "text": "and if you consider that the cerebral cortex",
            "start": 354.849,
            "duration": 2.081
        },
        {
            "text": "is the seat of functions like",
            "start": 356.93,
            "duration": 3.094
        },
        {
            "text": "awareness and logical and abstract reasoning,",
            "start": 360.024,
            "duration": 3.137
        },
        {
            "text": "and that 16 billion is the most neurons",
            "start": 363.161,
            "duration": 2.984
        },
        {
            "text": "that any cortex has,",
            "start": 366.145,
            "duration": 2.621
        },
        {
            "text": "I think this is the simplest explanation",
            "start": 368.766,
            "duration": 1.718
        },
        {
            "text": "for our remarkable cognitive abilities.",
            "start": 370.484,
            "duration": 3.142
        },
        {
            "text": "But just as important is what\nthe 86 billion neurons mean.",
            "start": 373.626,
            "duration": 3.221
        },
        {
            "text": "Because we found that the relationship",
            "start": 376.847,
            "duration": 1.529
        },
        {
            "text": "between the size of the brain\nand its number of neurons",
            "start": 378.376,
            "duration": 2.352
        },
        {
            "text": "could be described mathematically,",
            "start": 380.728,
            "duration": 1.627
        },
        {
            "text": "we could calculate what a human brain",
            "start": 382.355,
            "duration": 2.218
        },
        {
            "text": "would look like if it was made like a rodent brain.",
            "start": 384.573,
            "duration": 2.674
        },
        {
            "text": "So, a rodent brain with 86 billion neurons",
            "start": 387.247,
            "duration": 3.574
        },
        {
            "text": "would weigh 36 kilos.",
            "start": 390.821,
            "duration": 3.121
        },
        {
            "text": "That's not possible.",
            "start": 393.942,
            "duration": 1.633
        },
        {
            "text": "A brain that huge would be crushed",
            "start": 395.575,
            "duration": 1.906
        },
        {
            "text": "by its own weight,",
            "start": 397.481,
            "duration": 1.184
        },
        {
            "text": "and this impossible brain would go",
            "start": 398.665,
            "duration": 1.587
        },
        {
            "text": "in the body of 89 tons.",
            "start": 400.252,
            "duration": 3.771
        },
        {
            "text": "I don't think it looks like us.",
            "start": 404.023,
            "duration": 2.134
        },
        {
            "text": "So this brings us to a very important\nconclusion already,",
            "start": 406.157,
            "duration": 2.553
        },
        {
            "text": "which is that we are not rodents.",
            "start": 408.71,
            "duration": 2.647
        },
        {
            "text": "The human brain is not a large rat brain.",
            "start": 411.357,
            "duration": 3.268
        },
        {
            "text": "Compared to a rat, we might seem special, yes,",
            "start": 414.625,
            "duration": 2.628
        },
        {
            "text": "but that's not a fair comparison to make,",
            "start": 417.253,
            "duration": 2.22
        },
        {
            "text": "given that we know that we are not rodents.",
            "start": 419.473,
            "duration": 2.089
        },
        {
            "text": "We are primates,",
            "start": 421.562,
            "duration": 1.39
        },
        {
            "text": "so the correct comparison is to other primates.",
            "start": 422.952,
            "duration": 2.774
        },
        {
            "text": "And there, if you do the math,",
            "start": 425.726,
            "duration": 1.227
        },
        {
            "text": "you find that a generic primate",
            "start": 426.953,
            "duration": 2.786
        },
        {
            "text": "with 86 billion neurons",
            "start": 429.739,
            "duration": 1.93
        },
        {
            "text": "would have a brain of about 1.2 kilos,",
            "start": 431.669,
            "duration": 3.003
        },
        {
            "text": "which seems just right,",
            "start": 434.672,
            "duration": 1.889
        },
        {
            "text": "in a body of some 66 kilos,",
            "start": 436.561,
            "duration": 1.972
        },
        {
            "text": "which in my case is exactly right,",
            "start": 438.533,
            "duration": 2.645
        },
        {
            "text": "which brings us to a very unsurprising",
            "start": 441.178,
            "duration": 2.62
        },
        {
            "text": "but still incredibly important conclusion:",
            "start": 443.798,
            "duration": 2.969
        },
        {
            "text": "I am a primate.",
            "start": 446.767,
            "duration": 1.341
        },
        {
            "text": "And all of you are primates.",
            "start": 448.108,
            "duration": 2.698
        },
        {
            "text": "And so was Darwin.",
            "start": 450.806,
            "duration": 1.9
        },
        {
            "text": "I love to think that Darwin\nwould have really appreciated this.",
            "start": 452.706,
            "duration": 2.94
        },
        {
            "text": "His brain, like ours,",
            "start": 455.646,
            "duration": 1.967
        },
        {
            "text": "was made in the image of other primate brains.",
            "start": 457.613,
            "duration": 3.511
        },
        {
            "text": "So the human brain may be remarkable, yes,",
            "start": 461.124,
            "duration": 2.302
        },
        {
            "text": "but it is not special in its number of neurons.",
            "start": 463.426,
            "duration": 2.781
        },
        {
            "text": "It is just a large primate brain.",
            "start": 466.207,
            "duration": 1.855
        },
        {
            "text": "I think that's a very humbling and sobering thought",
            "start": 468.062,
            "duration": 3.044
        },
        {
            "text": "that should remind us of our place in nature.",
            "start": 471.106,
            "duration": 3.063
        },
        {
            "text": "Why does it cost so much energy, then?",
            "start": 474.169,
            "duration": 2.644
        },
        {
            "text": "Well, other people have figured out",
            "start": 476.813,
            "duration": 1.447
        },
        {
            "text": "how much energy the human brain",
            "start": 478.26,
            "duration": 1.503
        },
        {
            "text": "and that of other species costs,",
            "start": 479.763,
            "duration": 1.407
        },
        {
            "text": "and now that we knew how many neurons",
            "start": 481.17,
            "duration": 1.652
        },
        {
            "text": "each brain was made of, we could do the math.",
            "start": 482.822,
            "duration": 2.342
        },
        {
            "text": "And it turns out that both human",
            "start": 485.164,
            "duration": 1.866
        },
        {
            "text": "and other brains cost about the same,",
            "start": 487.03,
            "duration": 2.823
        },
        {
            "text": "an average of six calories \nper billion neurons per day.",
            "start": 489.853,
            "duration": 3.421
        },
        {
            "text": "So the total energetic cost of a brain",
            "start": 493.274,
            "duration": 2.139
        },
        {
            "text": "is a simple, linear function",
            "start": 495.413,
            "duration": 2.034
        },
        {
            "text": "of its number of neurons,",
            "start": 497.447,
            "duration": 1.709
        },
        {
            "text": "and it turns out that the human brain",
            "start": 499.156,
            "duration": 2.183
        },
        {
            "text": "costs just as much energy as you would expect.",
            "start": 501.339,
            "duration": 3.841
        },
        {
            "text": "So the reason why the human brain",
            "start": 505.18,
            "duration": 2.091
        },
        {
            "text": "costs so much energy is simply because",
            "start": 507.271,
            "duration": 1.672
        },
        {
            "text": "it has a huge number of neurons,",
            "start": 508.943,
            "duration": 1.983
        },
        {
            "text": "and because we are primates",
            "start": 510.926,
            "duration": 1.485
        },
        {
            "text": "with many more neurons for a given body size",
            "start": 512.411,
            "duration": 2.499
        },
        {
            "text": "than any other animal,",
            "start": 514.91,
            "duration": 1.522
        },
        {
            "text": "the relative cost of our brain is large,",
            "start": 516.432,
            "duration": 3.54
        },
        {
            "text": "but just because we're primates,\nnot because we're special.",
            "start": 519.972,
            "duration": 3.001
        },
        {
            "text": "Last question, then:",
            "start": 522.973,
            "duration": 1.19
        },
        {
            "text": "how did we come by this\nremarkable number of neurons,",
            "start": 524.163,
            "duration": 3.115
        },
        {
            "text": "and in particular, if great apes",
            "start": 527.278,
            "duration": 1.9
        },
        {
            "text": "are larger than we are,",
            "start": 529.178,
            "duration": 1.555
        },
        {
            "text": "why don't they have a larger brain \nthan we do, with more neurons?",
            "start": 530.733,
            "duration": 3.765
        },
        {
            "text": "When we realized how much expensive it is",
            "start": 534.498,
            "duration": 2.09
        },
        {
            "text": "to have a lot of neurons in the brain, I figured,",
            "start": 536.588,
            "duration": 2.333
        },
        {
            "text": "maybe there's a simple reason.",
            "start": 538.921,
            "duration": 2.003
        },
        {
            "text": "They just can't afford the energy",
            "start": 540.924,
            "duration": 1.683
        },
        {
            "text": "for both a large body \nand a large number of neurons.",
            "start": 542.607,
            "duration": 2.95
        },
        {
            "text": "So we did the math.",
            "start": 545.557,
            "duration": 1.429
        },
        {
            "text": "We calculated on the one hand",
            "start": 546.986,
            "duration": 1.6
        },
        {
            "text": "how much energy a primate gets per day",
            "start": 548.586,
            "duration": 1.941
        },
        {
            "text": "from eating raw foods,",
            "start": 550.527,
            "duration": 1.35
        },
        {
            "text": "and on the other hand, how much energy",
            "start": 551.877,
            "duration": 2.037
        },
        {
            "text": "a body of a certain size costs",
            "start": 553.914,
            "duration": 1.764
        },
        {
            "text": "and how much energy a brain of a\ncertain number of neurons costs,",
            "start": 555.678,
            "duration": 3.387
        },
        {
            "text": "and we looked for the combinations",
            "start": 559.065,
            "duration": 1.489
        },
        {
            "text": "of body size and number of brain neurons",
            "start": 560.554,
            "duration": 2.411
        },
        {
            "text": "that a primate could afford",
            "start": 562.965,
            "duration": 1.27
        },
        {
            "text": "if it ate a certain number of hours per day.",
            "start": 564.235,
            "duration": 2.548
        },
        {
            "text": "And what we found is that",
            "start": 566.783,
            "duration": 1.816
        },
        {
            "text": "because neurons are so expensive,",
            "start": 568.599,
            "duration": 1.712
        },
        {
            "text": "there is a tradeoff between\nbody size and number of neurons.",
            "start": 570.311,
            "duration": 3.37
        },
        {
            "text": "So a primate that eats eight hours per day",
            "start": 573.681,
            "duration": 2.951
        },
        {
            "text": "can afford at most 53 billion neurons,",
            "start": 576.632,
            "duration": 3.024
        },
        {
            "text": "but then its body cannot be any bigger",
            "start": 579.656,
            "duration": 1.727
        },
        {
            "text": "than 25 kilos.",
            "start": 581.383,
            "duration": 1.954
        },
        {
            "text": "To weigh any more than that,",
            "start": 583.337,
            "duration": 1.701
        },
        {
            "text": "it has to give up neurons.",
            "start": 585.038,
            "duration": 1.769
        },
        {
            "text": "So it's either a large body",
            "start": 586.807,
            "duration": 2.653
        },
        {
            "text": "or a large number of neurons.",
            "start": 589.46,
            "duration": 1.495
        },
        {
            "text": "When you eat like a primate,",
            "start": 590.955,
            "duration": 1.365
        },
        {
            "text": "you can't afford both.",
            "start": 592.32,
            "duration": 2.236
        },
        {
            "text": "One way out of this metabolic limitation",
            "start": 594.556,
            "duration": 1.964
        },
        {
            "text": "would be to spend even more hours per day eating,",
            "start": 596.52,
            "duration": 3.401
        },
        {
            "text": "but that gets dangerous,",
            "start": 599.921,
            "duration": 1.363
        },
        {
            "text": "and past a certain point, it's just not possible.",
            "start": 601.284,
            "duration": 2.719
        },
        {
            "text": "Gorillas and orangutans, for instance,",
            "start": 604.003,
            "duration": 1.537
        },
        {
            "text": "afford about 30 billion neurons",
            "start": 605.54,
            "duration": 1.923
        },
        {
            "text": "by spending eight and a half hours per day eating,",
            "start": 607.463,
            "duration": 2.966
        },
        {
            "text": "and that seems to be about as much as they can do.",
            "start": 610.429,
            "duration": 3.116
        },
        {
            "text": "Nine hours of feeding per day",
            "start": 613.545,
            "duration": 1.791
        },
        {
            "text": "seems to be the practical limit for a primate.",
            "start": 615.336,
            "duration": 3.271
        },
        {
            "text": "What about us?",
            "start": 618.607,
            "duration": 1.791
        },
        {
            "text": "With our 86 billion neurons",
            "start": 620.398,
            "duration": 1.6
        },
        {
            "text": "and 60 to 70 kilos of body mass,",
            "start": 621.998,
            "duration": 3.035
        },
        {
            "text": "we should have to spend over nine hours",
            "start": 625.033,
            "duration": 3.561
        },
        {
            "text": "per day every single day feeding,",
            "start": 628.594,
            "duration": 3.575
        },
        {
            "text": "which is just not feasible.",
            "start": 632.169,
            "duration": 2.039
        },
        {
            "text": "If we ate like a primate,",
            "start": 634.208,
            "duration": 1.834
        },
        {
            "text": "we should not be here.",
            "start": 636.042,
            "duration": 2.253
        },
        {
            "text": "How did we get here, then?",
            "start": 638.295,
            "duration": 2.127
        },
        {
            "text": "Well, if our brain costs just as much energy",
            "start": 640.422,
            "duration": 2.735
        },
        {
            "text": "as it should, and if we can't spend",
            "start": 643.157,
            "duration": 1.723
        },
        {
            "text": "every waking hour of the day feeding,",
            "start": 644.88,
            "duration": 3.674
        },
        {
            "text": "then the only alternative, really,",
            "start": 648.554,
            "duration": 1.911
        },
        {
            "text": "is to somehow get more energy",
            "start": 650.465,
            "duration": 1.958
        },
        {
            "text": "out of the same foods.",
            "start": 652.423,
            "duration": 1.953
        },
        {
            "text": "And remarkably, that matches exactly",
            "start": 654.376,
            "duration": 3.8
        },
        {
            "text": "what our ancestors are believed to have invented",
            "start": 658.176,
            "duration": 3.037
        },
        {
            "text": "one and a half million years ago,",
            "start": 661.213,
            "duration": 1.839
        },
        {
            "text": "when they invented cooking.",
            "start": 663.052,
            "duration": 2.782
        },
        {
            "text": "To cook is to use fire",
            "start": 665.834,
            "duration": 1.97
        },
        {
            "text": "to pre-digest foods outside of your body.",
            "start": 667.804,
            "duration": 3.8
        },
        {
            "text": "Cooked foods are softer, so they're easier to chew",
            "start": 671.604,
            "duration": 2.606
        },
        {
            "text": "and to turn completely into mush in your mouth,",
            "start": 674.21,
            "duration": 2.563
        },
        {
            "text": "so that allows them to be completely digested",
            "start": 676.773,
            "duration": 2.152
        },
        {
            "text": "and absorbed in your gut,",
            "start": 678.925,
            "duration": 1.436
        },
        {
            "text": "which makes them yield much more\nenergy in much less time.",
            "start": 680.361,
            "duration": 3.655
        },
        {
            "text": "So cooking frees time for us to do",
            "start": 684.016,
            "duration": 2.489
        },
        {
            "text": "much more interesting things with our day",
            "start": 686.505,
            "duration": 2.062
        },
        {
            "text": "and with our neurons",
            "start": 688.567,
            "duration": 1.48
        },
        {
            "text": "than just thinking about food,",
            "start": 690.047,
            "duration": 1.905
        },
        {
            "text": "looking for food, and gobbling down food",
            "start": 691.952,
            "duration": 1.704
        },
        {
            "text": "all day long.",
            "start": 693.656,
            "duration": 1.225
        },
        {
            "text": "So because of cooking, what once was",
            "start": 694.881,
            "duration": 2.499
        },
        {
            "text": "a major liability, this large,",
            "start": 697.38,
            "duration": 2.353
        },
        {
            "text": "dangerously expensive brain with a lot of neurons,",
            "start": 699.733,
            "duration": 3.033
        },
        {
            "text": "could now become a major asset,",
            "start": 702.766,
            "duration": 2.036
        },
        {
            "text": "now that we could both afford \nthe energy for a lot of neurons",
            "start": 704.802,
            "duration": 3.251
        },
        {
            "text": "and the time to do interesting things with them.",
            "start": 708.056,
            "duration": 2.503
        },
        {
            "text": "So I think this explains why the human brain",
            "start": 710.559,
            "duration": 1.974
        },
        {
            "text": "grew to become so large so fast in evolution,",
            "start": 712.533,
            "duration": 3.24
        },
        {
            "text": "all of the while remaining just a primate brain.",
            "start": 715.773,
            "duration": 3.897
        },
        {
            "text": "With this large brain now affordable by cooking,",
            "start": 719.67,
            "duration": 2.774
        },
        {
            "text": "we went rapidly from raw foods to culture,",
            "start": 722.444,
            "duration": 2.913
        },
        {
            "text": "agriculture, civilization, grocery stores,",
            "start": 725.357,
            "duration": 2.606
        },
        {
            "text": "electricity, refrigerators,",
            "start": 727.963,
            "duration": 1.625
        },
        {
            "text": "all of those things that nowadays",
            "start": 729.588,
            "duration": 1.607
        },
        {
            "text": "allow us to get all the energy we need",
            "start": 731.195,
            "duration": 2.042
        },
        {
            "text": "for the whole day in a single sitting",
            "start": 733.237,
            "duration": 2.782
        },
        {
            "text": "at your favorite fast food joint.",
            "start": 736.019,
            "duration": 2.954
        },
        {
            "text": "So what once was a solution",
            "start": 738.973,
            "duration": 2.437
        },
        {
            "text": "now became the problem,",
            "start": 741.41,
            "duration": 1.699
        },
        {
            "text": "and ironically, we look for the solution in raw food.",
            "start": 743.109,
            "duration": 5.517
        },
        {
            "text": "So what is the human advantage?",
            "start": 748.626,
            "duration": 2.556
        },
        {
            "text": "What is it that we have",
            "start": 751.182,
            "duration": 1.503
        },
        {
            "text": "that no other animal has?",
            "start": 752.685,
            "duration": 2.535
        },
        {
            "text": "My answer is that we have the largest number",
            "start": 755.22,
            "duration": 2.348
        },
        {
            "text": "of neurons in the cerebral cortex,",
            "start": 757.568,
            "duration": 1.472
        },
        {
            "text": "and I think that's the simplest explanation",
            "start": 759.04,
            "duration": 1.844
        },
        {
            "text": "for our remarkable cognitive abilities.",
            "start": 760.884,
            "duration": 2.013
        },
        {
            "text": "And what is it that we do that no other animal does,",
            "start": 762.897,
            "duration": 3.227
        },
        {
            "text": "and which I believe was fundamental",
            "start": 766.124,
            "duration": 1.969
        },
        {
            "text": "to allow us to reach that large,",
            "start": 768.093,
            "duration": 3.083
        },
        {
            "text": "largest number of neurons in the cortex?",
            "start": 771.176,
            "duration": 2.222
        },
        {
            "text": "In two words, we cook.",
            "start": 773.398,
            "duration": 2.215
        },
        {
            "text": "No other animal cooks its food. Only humans do.",
            "start": 775.613,
            "duration": 3.566
        },
        {
            "text": "And I think that's how we got to become human.",
            "start": 779.179,
            "duration": 2.87
        },
        {
            "text": "Studying the human brain changed \nthe way I think about food.",
            "start": 782.049,
            "duration": 2.46
        },
        {
            "text": "I now look at my kitchen,",
            "start": 784.509,
            "duration": 1.645
        },
        {
            "text": "and I bow to it,",
            "start": 786.154,
            "duration": 1.47
        },
        {
            "text": "and I thank my ancestors for coming up",
            "start": 787.624,
            "duration": 1.705
        },
        {
            "text": "with the invention that probably made us humans.",
            "start": 789.329,
            "duration": 1.9
        },
        {
            "text": "Thank you very much.",
            "start": 791.229,
            "duration": 2.132
        },
        {
            "text": "(Applause)",
            "start": 793.361,
            "duration": 6.353
        }
    ],
    "video_id": "_7_XH1CBzGw"
}
